						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">c. 14th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Refers to some bad incident involving the death of some person taking poison and some decision made by the temple trustees invoking a copper-plate charter supposed to be available at Perumbaṟṟappuliyūr (Chidambaram). Refers to some Mahabharatha related story of poisonous pond <hi rend="italic">(nachchuppoykai).</hi> </p>						

